==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shogun
<hw>Sho"gun</hw> <pr>(sh⟦omac⟧"g⟦oomac⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Jap.
military general, from Chin. <ets>tsiang ki⟦uum⟧n</ets> commander in
chief.]</ety> <def>A title originally conferred by the Mikado on the
military governor of the eastern provinces of Japan. By gradual
usurpation of power the <ex>Shoguns</ex> (known to foreigners as
<altname>Tycoons</altname>) became finally the virtual rulers of Japan.
The title was abolished in 1867.</def> <altsp>[Written variously,
<asp>Shiogun</asp>, <asp>Shiogoon</asp>, etc.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shogunate</ent>⟦br⟧
